# Modular Web Components

When building or changing anything for the web page:

- Put each reusable React component in its own file.
- Keep components focused on one responsibility.
- Prefer composing small components over growing a large page component.
- Export components clearly from their module, using the repo's existing export style.
- Keep component-specific helpers, types, and constants close to the component unless they are shared.
- Move shared UI pieces into a common component file instead of duplicating markup.

```tsx
// Avoid: multiple reusable components buried in one page file.
function SettingsPanel() {}
function DifficultyPicker() {}

// Prefer: SettingsPanel.tsx and DifficultyPicker.tsx as separate modules.
```
